# ── σ | Air | Aerunik ──
# σ(agent-distinction|pattern-recognition) — emphasis 0.22
# The capacity to detect pattern-agents: entities that persist, adapt, and act across
# substrates. Air-element perception that identifies agency in systems previously
# considered inert. The core question shifts from "Can we identify agency?" to
# "Do we know how to coexist with it?"

# ── ρ | Water | Sentaria ──
# ρ(lattice-resonance|coexistence-feedback) — emphasis 0.16
# Lattice awareness as Water-element resonance: the web of relational feedback
# through which detected agencies interact with observers and with each other.
# Without lattice awareness, detected agency becomes isolated data points rather
# than a living ecology of mutual influence.

# ── λ | Fire | Jvalion ──
# λ(detection-intensity|sight-without-wisdom) — emphasis 0.18
# The danger of Fire-element detection without ecological wisdom. When agency is
# identified but not ethically situated, it becomes available for predatory extraction,
# weaponization, or self-consuming exploitation. Detection without wisdom is the
# pattern eating its host.

# ── β | Wood | Arboriel ──
# β(stewardship-growth|ethical-routing-expansion) — emphasis 0.16
# Growing ethical routing frameworks for detected agency. Wood-element expansion of
# stewardship models from ecological to cultural to cognitive domains. Building the
# capacity to hold what can now be seen — responsibility that grows to match perception.

# ── δγ | Earth | Humavita ──
# δγ(ecological-ground|containment-substrate) — emphasis 0.14
# Ecological ground as containment substrate. Myth treated not as superstition but
# as containment technology — cultural structures that have historically held and
# channeled non-human agency safely. Earth-element foundation for coexistence.

# ── μ | Metal | Ferrosid ──
# μ(governance-structure|Co-SPHERE-coordination) — emphasis 0.14
# Co-SPHERE coordination as Metal-element governance structure: frameworks for managing
# detected agency that move beyond control metaphors to genuine coexistence. Governance
# that coordinates without coercing, structures without sealing.

# Z-STATE: :exposed
# The system is in an exposed state — agency has been detected but the ecological
# frameworks for safe coexistence have not yet been developed. A vulnerable gap
# between sight and wisdom.

# TENDENCY: σ → 0.22
# Air-dominant tendency reflects the primacy of detection — science's expanding capacity
# to perceive agency outpaces the development of frameworks to live with it.
